{
  "stem": "9701.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember whispering to my mother, I want to get out of here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And not just out of this wardrobe, but I want to get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I guess the reason I said I want to get out of Germany is because I knew that my parents had tried but had not been successful in leaving Germany.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I don't really know how long we sat in that wardrobe.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It seemed at the time it was a lifetime.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When it was quiet for a while, we decided that it was probably safe to come down.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Actually they had done very little damage to my aunt's house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We later learned that all the actions against Jews on that day in our village had been called to a halt at noon.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they must have come to my aunt's house maybe a minute or two before noon.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There were a number of other things that happened that day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Jewish businesses, for instance, were permanently closed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If you were Jewish and a doctor, a dentist, or an attorney, you weren't allowed to practice.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Christian doctors weren't allowed to treat Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Jews weren't allowed to go to a hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In other words, a lot of the civil rights that people today, that I today, take for granted were taken away from Jews and were taken away permanently.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Most of the synagogues all over Germany and Austria, and Austria by that time had already been annexed to Germany, were burned.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They did burn the synagogue, or they started to set the synagogue on fire in our village, but very quickly extinguished the fire because the buildings on either side of the synagogue were Christian homes and were very close by.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
